<br>
A good bard will handle a caster.<br>
<br>
  Any bard that knows what he is doing will dispel you and kill you. Hopeless to beat a bard if he has good enough resist gear to prevent himself from being snared. He moves so fast you cant hit him with a spell unless he is coming in to kill you.  He will play hit and run with a caster running in and dispelling and running out without a caster being able to cast on him.  If the caster is has a right clickable item and is smart enough to use it to beat the dispelling action he will just be on you meleeing and dispilling.   Only way a caster can kill a bard is if the bard makes a mistake or if the caster sneaks up on him. The statement is assuming that the levels are the same.<br>
<br>
Wizzies. hmmm. The higher you go in levels and abilities the less likely the chance of being able to beat him. Wizzies are the complete opposite of druids. They start a little weak and continue to get power as they level and by the time they are 60 they are easily a master of their role. Fast Damage output.<br>
<br>
 The druid class is suffering from its own dot.  Over time the druid class is getting weaker as the other classes are getting stronger.  In every aspect of game play.  Even in the aspect of the expansions in EQ.  <br>
<br>
 Since this is imo and im responding to someones input im not going to argue with anyone about my experiences with the classes.<br>
<br>
  All my play time is on a pvp server. If everything is equal you will not beat those 3 classes and as you level the possiblity to beat them decreases until the point of not even having a chance.  IE the perfect example is manburn and lifetap.  You just dont have the skills they have.  They have fast and vast damage output that you cant compete with. By the time you realize you need to heal (one spell) it might be too late.  I get hit for over a thousand damage from one cast by necros and wizzies all the time.      <br>
